2. useEffect() Hook
-------------------
* The useEffect hook in React is a powerful tool for handling side effects in functional components.
* Side effects may include data fetching, DOM manipulation, subscriptions, or any other asynchronous tasks that need to be executed after rendering
* useEffect replaces lifecycle methods such as componentDidMount(empty dep), componentDidUpdate(with dep), and componentWillUnmount(cleanup function) in class components

Why do we need it?
------------------

* Fetching data:- fetch data from API's when component mounts or when dependencies change
* Subscriptions: subscribe to events, sockets, or external stores and clean up on unmount.
* Timers:- set timeouts/intervals and clear them to avoid memory leaks.
* DOM Manipulation:- Interact with DOM API's (focus, scroll, measurements, etc)
* Local storage/Session storage:- sync state with browser storage


syntax
-------
useEffect (setup, dependencies?)
---------------------------------

* Effect function → runs after render
* Cleanup function → runs before effect re-runs or component unmounts
* Dependency array → controls when the effect runs
* If omitted → runs after every render

Syntax:
------
useEffect (() => {
    //side effect code here
    return () => {
        //cleanup code here (optional)
    }}
), ([dependencies]);


Types os UseEffect
-------------------
1. No Dependency Array

    useEffect(()=>{
    console.log('run after every render') })

* Runs after every render (initial + updates)
* Use with caution! Can cause infinite loops
* Render → effect(every time)

2. Empty Dependency Array

    useEffect(()=>{
    console.log('run only once when component mounts')
    }, [])

* Runs only once after the initial render(like componentDidMount)
* Cleanup runs on unmount.
* Render(initial) → Effect(once)

3. With Dependencies

    useEffect(()=>{
    console.log('run when count changes')
    }, [count])

* Runs after initial render and whenever count value changes.
* Cleanup runs before re running the effect.
* Render Effect(when count changes)

4. Cleanup (Return)

    useEffect(() => {
    console.log("Component Mounted");
    return () => {
        console.log("Component Unmounted");
    };
    }, []);

* Runs before the effect re-runs and when the component unmounts
* Before re-runs/Unmount -> cleanup -->